The paper discusses the use of SWRL and SPIN in developing rule-based applications on top of ontologies, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of ontology editors and reasoners, which are tools commonly used in the field of Databases (cs.DB). The paper deals with Semantic Web models and Linked Open Data, which are topics related to the sub-category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the use of rule engines and the transformation of rules, which are topics related to Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Programming Languages (cs.PL).
